com.dynatrace.openkit.api

Interface WebRequestTag


  • public interface WebRequestTag
    This interface allows tagging and timing of a web request.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getTag()
      Returns the Dynatrace tag which has to be set manually as Dynatrace HTTP header (OpenKit.WEBREQUEST_TAG_HEADER).
      void setResponseCode(int responseCode)
      Sets the response code of this web request.
      void startTiming()
      Starts the web request timing.
      void stopTiming()
      Stops the web request timing.

    • Method Detail

      • getTag

        java.lang.String getTag()
        Returns the Dynatrace tag which has to be set manually as Dynatrace HTTP header (OpenKit.WEBREQUEST_TAG_HEADER).
        This is only necessary for tagging web requests via 3rd party HTTP clients.
        Returns:
        the Dynatrace tag to be set as HTTP header value or an empty String if capture is off

      • setResponseCode

        void setResponseCode(int responseCode)
        Sets the response code of this web request. Has to be called before stopTiming().
        Parameters:
        responseCode - response code of this web request

      • startTiming

        void startTiming()
        Starts the web request timing. Should be called when the web request is initiated.

      • stopTiming

        void stopTiming()
        Stops the web request timing. Should be called when the web request is finished.
